This space is inaccessible to and hidden from players! Members of the DmGroup may access this content.
**Note:** The style for this space is distinct from the [[Player space>>doc:Player.WebHome]] to avoid confusion as to who can access specific content.
== General Topics ==
General information and background knowledge of Erithnoi.
* [[History >>doc:Erithnoi History]]- The history of Erithnoi. * [[Cosmology>>doc:Cosmology]] - The cosmology of the world of Erth. * [[Geography>>doc:Geography]] - The geography of Erithnoi. * [[Religion>>doc:Cosmology]] - The gods of Erth. * [[Races>>doc:Player.Races]] - Intelligent races of Erithnoi. * [[Calendar>>doc:Player.Calendar]] - The seasons, the sky, and related things. * [[Languages>>doc:Player.Languages]] - The languages of Erithnoi. * [[Organizations>>doc:Organizations]] - Organizations of Erithnoi. * [[Monsters>>doc:Monsters]] - Monsters unique to Erithnoi. * [[NPCs>>doc:NPCs]] - Some major NPCs of Erithnoi. * [[Magic Items>>doc:MagicItems]] - Items and artifacts specific to Erithnoi. * [[General Knowledge>>doc:GeneralKnowledge]] - General catch-all for other articles about Erithnoi. * [[Fragments>>doc:Fragments]] - Incomplete stuff and design notes.
== Campaigns ==
Various campaigns which are active or have been run in Erithnoi.
* [[Kinergh Campaign>>doc:KinerghCampaign]] - Gillian, Tara, and Nate. Run online from 2008-2011. * [[Midrealms Campaign>>doc:MidrealmsCampaign]] - Krystal, Tim, Don, and List. The 'Tuesday Night Group'. * fall crest Campaign * [[Eldoran Isles Campaign>>doc:EldoranIslesCampaign]] - Tara and Gillian in the Eldoran Isles pirate campaign. * [[Third Midrealms Campaign>>doc:ThirdMidrealmsCampaign]] - Tara and Gillian in The Midrealms/Fallcrest.
== Geography and Locations ==
Locations in Erithnoi. This is for DM info on locations, player info should go in the player space and can be linked to from these articles.
* [[Kinergh>>doc:Kinergh]] - Locations in Kinergh and some surrounding areas. * [[Midrealms>>doc:Midrealms]] - Locations in the Midrealms and some surrounding areas.
